<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 2:16PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Toombs,
south central Emanuel, northeastern Wheeler and Montgomery Counties
through 245 PM EDT...
At 215 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Ailey, or near Mount
Vernon, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lyons, Mount Vernon, Vidalia, Glenwood, Oak Park, Ailey, Higgston,
Santa Claus, Tarrytown, Center, Ohoopee, Ponderosa, Kibbee, and
Normantown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
